    {
      "id": "CVE-2024-7348",
      "source": "postgresql",
      "title": "PostgreSQL relation replacement during pg_dump executes arbitrary SQL",
      "description": "An attacker able to create and drop non-temporary objects could inject SQL code\nthat would be executed by a concurrent\npg_dump\nsession with the privileges of the role running\npg_dump\n(which is often a\nsuperuser). The attack involves replacing a sequence or similar object with a\nview or foreign table that will execute malicious code. To prevent this,\nintroduce a new server parameter\nrestrict_nonsystem_relation_kind\nthat can\ndisable expansion of non-builtin views as well as access to foreign table",
      "severity": "high",
